node.text:
Directed and shot by @alivelikethewind, @beyondthebeat, @windcollective (@alivelikethewind) “This video is a celebration of black culture. You see, the beauty, the power, the energy that we possess is just as important a narrative right now. I’m committed to sharing more of our heart and blessing this world with our perspective.
.
I dreamed up this video with the @windcollective team and we had to make it. We shot it across several Wind Collective Travel Experiences Im 2019. I remember feeling blessed to capture and share the energy of my people.
.
Black people - It may be our time to mourn but it is also our time to be joyful because change is coming. It may be our time to march in the streets and it also our time to stand bold, proud of who we are. My black kings and queens - there is a renaissance occurring. Stay woke and stay vibesy. Love you all.”
.
Here’s a reminder from the script of the video - “Being Black. It’s not mediocre. Nor is it a limit. Its your greatest asset. Your secret weapon. It’s history, and struggle and rising. It’s beauty and birthright and excellence. We are the culture - In Black.”

node.title: Being Black - We are the Culture
